                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/233: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1" type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-03T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 3, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 3—6:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Kuo Min agency, Nanking, reports August 2: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Ministry of Finance having received report from Inspector General of
                            Customs that a remittance of Shanghai taels 843,675.44 has been received
                            from Dairen branch of Yokohama Specie Bank representing <pb facs="0290"
                                n="192" xml:id="pg_192"/> about one-third of the customs revenue
                            detained before the seizure of the Manchurian customs, the Japanese
                            portion of the Boxer Indemnity held in suspense in the Hong Kong and
                            Shanghai Bank has been released.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Inspectorate General confirms correctness of the foregoing.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
